u get a basic amount and extra (known as &lsquo;elements&rsquo;) on top of this. </p>\n\n<p>How much you get depends on things like your circumstances and income. </p>\n\n<p>The basic amount is up to £1,920 a year. </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Element</th>\n      <th>Amount</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>You&rsquo;re a couple applying together</td>\n      <td>Up to £1,950 a year</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>You&rsquo;re a single parent</td>\n      <td>Up to £1,950 a year</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>You work at least 30 hours week</td>\n      <td>Up to £790 a year</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>You have a disability</td>\n      <td>Up to £2,790 a year</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>You have a severe disability</td>\n      <td>Up to £1,190 a year (on top of the disability payment)</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>You pay for <a href=\"/childcare-tax-credits\" title=\"Childcare and tax credits\">approved childcare</a></td>\n      <td>Up to £122.50 (1 child) or £210 (2 or more children) a week</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Use the <a href=\"/tax-credits-calculator\" title=\"Tax credits calculator\">tax credit calculator</a> to work out how much you could get.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How you&rsquo;re paid</h2>\n\n<p>Money is paid directly into your bank or building society account, every week or 4 weeks.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re a couple, you must choose one account. </p>\n\n<p>Usually, you&rsquo;re paid from the date of your claim up to the end of the tax year (5 April). </p>\n\n<h2>If your circumstances change</h2>\n\n<p>Your tax credits you get can go up or down if your family or work life change - you must <a href=\"/changes-affect-tax-credits\" title=\"Changes that affect your tax credits\">report these changes</a> to the Tax Credit Office. For example, you start a new job, go on maternity leave or you&rsquo;re laid off work. </p